# Licensing

This repository is dual-licensed. The license that applies depends on which
part of the repository you are using.

## Documentation and specification text

The specification and documentation — everything under `spec/`, `proposals/`,
and `content/`, and all other prose — is licensed under the
**Creative Commons Attribution 4.0 International License (CC-BY-4.0)**.

See [`LICENSES/CC-BY-4.0.txt`](LICENSES/CC-BY-4.0.txt).

## Code and schemas

Source code, JSON Schemas (everything under `schemas/`), site configuration,
build tooling, and any reference implementations in this repository are
licensed under the **Apache License, Version 2.0**.

See [`LICENSES/Apache-2.0.txt`](LICENSES/Apache-2.0.txt).

## SPDX

Where practical, individual files carry an `SPDX-License-Identifier` header of
either `CC-BY-4.0` or `Apache-2.0` to remove ambiguity.

## Patent grant

The Apache-2.0 license covering the schemas and code includes an express,
royalty-free patent grant. The project does not pursue restrictive patents
over the protocol; contributions are accepted on the understanding that they
may be implemented royalty-free. See [`CONTRIBUTING.md`](CONTRIBUTING.md).
